  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason : 1 - The proposed building by reason of its siting, scale, massing and architecture would relate poorly to the local townscape and unacceptable harm would be caused to the setting of the adjoining locally listed Jolly Gardeners public house, contrary to the provisions of the National Planning Policy Framework, London Plan (2021) policies D3 and D4, and Development Management Policies Document (2016) policies DMS1 and DMS2.  ",
    "Reason : 2 - A substandard level of accommodation would be provided for future occupiers of flat 3 given its undersized nature, contrary to the minimum Nationally Described Space Standards and Development Management Policies Document (2016) policy DMH6. ",
    "Reason : 3 - The intensification of the residential use of the site and the siting of habitable rooms and external amenity space would likely prejudice the current and future function of the adjoining Jolly Gardeners public house and the Locally Significant Industrial Area, contrary to the provisions of London Plan (2021) policy D13.",
    "Reason : 4 - The proposal includes the demolition of the existing building and the site is located in close proximity to the River Wandle and King Georges Park Sites of Importance for Nature Conservation (SINC), and there has been a failure to demonstrate the potential ecological impacts of the development or the means to secure on-site biodiversity enhancements, contrary to the provisions of policy DMO4 of the Councils adopted Development Management Policies Document (2016).  ",
    "Reason : 5 - In dealing with this application the Council has implemented the requirement in the National Planning Policy Framework to work with the applicant in a positive and proactive manner and the Council has, as far as practicable, sought solutions to problems arising in relation to dealing with the planning application. We have made available detailed advice in the form of our statutory policies in the Local Plan consisting of the Core Strategy, Development Management Policies Document, Supplementary Planning documents and where appropriate the Site Specific Allocations Document as well as offering a full pre application advice service, in order to ensure that the applicant has been given every opportunity to submit an application which is likely to be considered favourably. In addition further guidance was offered to the applicant by the case officer during the processing of the application to identify amendments to address those elements of the scheme considered unacceptable. However, the necessary amendments to make the application acceptable are substantial and would materially change the development proposal. They would require further consultations to be undertaken prior to determination, which could not take place within the statutory determination period specified by the Department of Communities and Local Government. You are therefore encouraged to consider submission of a fresh application incorporating the material amendments set out below which are necessary to make the scheme acceptable. \r\n\r\nRequired amendments:\r\n1. Consider the local context in greater detail and revisit the design, scale and massing of the proposed building.\r\n2. Ensure all dwellings accord with the Nationally Described Space Standards.\r\n3. Relocate the development away from the boundary and reconsider the location of habitable rooms and external terraces, and come forward with a development that does not result in the substantial intensification of residential development on site.  \r\n4. Sub"
  ],
